<TITLE> Cabinet decides to overhaul Bakhrabad </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 19 (bdnews24.com)  The government has decided to overhaul the Bakhrabad Gas System Limited to develop the gas-run industries and the quality of service, a spokesman said on Sunday. It will set up the Bakhrabad Gas Distribution Company Ltd and the Karnaphuly Gas Distribution Company Ltd, according to a proposal approved at the meeting of the council of advisers on Sunday. The meeting was chaired by chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed Syed Fahim Munaim, press secretary to the chief adviser, in a briefing told newsmen that the area of Bakhrbad Gas Distribution Company Ltd would comprise Comilla, Chandpur, Brahmanbaria and greater Noakhali. The Karnaphuly Gas Distribution Company Ltd ( KGDCL) will cover Greater Chittagong and Chittagong Hill Tracts, with its office in Chittagong. The chief adviser on August 3 promised the people of Chittagong that the Karnaphuly gas company would be set up. The interim cabinet also approved the Local Government Pourashabha Ordinance (Amendment) 2008 and Local Government City Corporation Ordinance (Amendment) 2008. The press secretary said under the amendment punishment for electoral offence is six months at the minimum and seven years maximum. Besides, for violation of the electoral code of conduct, punishment of six months in prison and a fine of Tk 50,000 or both have been prescribed. Appeal time for election case has been reduced from 120 days to 30 days. Besides, NOC-BAN Ordinance-2008 of the Bangladesh National Olympic Committee has been placed with the council of advisers. It was sent back for further scrutiny for presentation to the council of advisers again. The meeting discussed the hajj flights that begin on Oct. 31, and melamine in powdered milk. The civil aviation ministry has been instructed to see whether it will be possible to carry hajj pilgrims from Sylhet and Chittagong. bdnews
